{{Infobox video game | title = Dogfight 1951 | collapsible = | state = | image = File:Dogfight 1951.png | caption = | developer = [[Treehouse Ltd]] | publisher = | series = | engine = | platforms = iOS | released = July 28, 2010 | genre = Aeroplane dog-fighting | modes = }}
'''''Dogfight 1951''''' (aka '''''1951: World War One''''') is an [[iOS]] game developed by Finnish indie studio [[Treehouse Ltd]] and released on July 28, 2010.
==Critical reception== The game has a Metacritic score of 86% based on 5 critic reviews.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/ios/dogfight-1951|title=Dogfight 1951|work=Metacritic}}</ref>
AppSpy said " 1951 - World War One is a classic war-era dog-fighting title with a rock'n roll attitude that can only get better with time. "<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.appspy.com/1951-world-war-one-review |accessdate=October 11, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120220091102/http://www.appspy.com/1951-world-war-one-review |archivedate=February 20, 2012 }}</ref> TouchGen said "World War One (1951) is a great purchase for anyone who enjoys aircraft games, shooters and anything with XP and level up elements in it. With its great implementation of controls and stunning visuals, it's a must buy! "<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.touchgen.net/1951-world-war-one |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-10-11 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130605143922/http://www.touchgen.net/1951-world-war-one |archivedate=2013-06-05 |df= }}</ref> 148Apps said " If you are up to a brisk, "top down RPG-ish plane shooter" challenge, then 1951 – World War One may be the perfect game for you. It plays well and it is pretty… what more do you want from an iPhone game? "<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.148apps.com/reviews/1951-world-war-review/|title=1951 - World War One Review|work=148Apps}}</ref> AppSmile wrote "With its stylish presentation, RPG elements, and engaging controls, 1951 creates an exciting combat experience. "<ref>http://www.appsmile.com/2010/08/14/1951-world-war-one-review/</ref> SlideToPlay said "It may not alter the course of history, but this fun flying and shooting game is great for a few hours."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slidetoplay.com/review/1951-world-war-one-review/|title=Dogfight 1951 Review|publisher=Slide To Play}}</ref>
