{{italic title}} '''''Hebdogiciel''''' was a [[French language|French]] [[computer magazine]] which was published from 1983 until January 1987.<ref>[http://www.acbm.com/virus/num_02/hebdogiciel.html Interview ''Hebdogiciel: 10 years after''] ''Le Virus Informatique'' Nr. 2. May 1997</ref><ref>[http://eaglesystem.free.fr/hebdo.html Explanations about the end of the magazine] by Gérard Ceccaldi, director of publication. ''Tilt'' magazine, 1988. (reprint)</ref> It was printed in a newspaper style format and focused on [[8-bit|8-]] and [[16-bit]] [[home computer]]s of the time, such as the [[Commodore 64]], [[ZX80]], [[Amstrad]], and others.
Each issue was a collection of both news articles on computer and software testing, treated satirically, and listings of [[source code]] which could be typed in by the reader.
