{{EngvarB|date=November 2015}} {{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}}
'''Myanmar Radio and Television 4''', known as '''MRTV-4''', is a [[Burma|Burmese]] [[State media|state-owned]] television station and satellite television. It consists of 16 local channels and 154 foreign channels.
==Channel details== The channel was launched in May 2004.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2004-05/13/content_1467206.htm|title=Myanmar to launch new TV channel |date=13 May 2004|publisher=[[Xinhua]]}}</ref> The channel is jointly operated by MRTV and the Forever Group, broadcasting programs between 7{{nbsp}}am and 11{{nbsp}}pm.<ref name=mt>{{cite news|url=http://www.mmtimes.com/feature/electronic/e09.htm|title=Broadcasting options expanding|last=Thaw|first=May|date=12 March 2007|publisher=''[[The Myanmar Times]]''|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203194721/http://www.mmtimes.com/feature/electronic/e09.htm|archivedate=3 December 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref> However, it is only available to viewers with MMBox satellite or terrestrial DVB-T receivers.<ref name=mt/>
The channel is run under the [[Ministry of Information (Burma)|Ministry of Information]], and international news broadcasts undergo [[Censorship in Burma|censorship]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.irrawaddy.org/article.php?art_id=15138|title=Burmese Junta Sees Satellite TV as Threat|last=Moe|first=Wai|date=18 February 2009|publisher=''[[The Irrawaddy]]''|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100812055638/http://irrawaddy.org/article.php?art_id=15138|archivedate=12 August 2010|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
Today, MRTV-4 broadcasts 24 hours a day.<ref>[http://www.mrtv4.net.mm/?url=sch1&scheduleday=5&week=1 MRTV-4's schedule] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120327060831/http://www.mrtv4.net.mm/?url=sch1&scheduleday=5&week=1 |date=27 March 2012 }}</ref>
