{{Infobox Company | name = Software Dynamics | logo = | type = [[Privately held]] | genre = Software utilities, browsers and games | foundation = 1987 | founder = [[Bill Stewart (programmer)|Bill Stewart]] | location_city = [[Victoria, BC]] | location_country = [[Canada]] | location = | locations = | area_served = | key_people = | industry = [[Software]] | products = [[After Dark (software)|After Dark]] | services = Software development, publishing, UX/UI design | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = [[Dynamic Karma|Dynamic Karma, inc.]] | homepage = | footnotes = }} '''Software Dynamics''' is a software development house, founded in 1987. They helped create the screen saver genre with #1 shareware Magic ScreenSaver and its successor, #1 selling commercial application ''[[After Dark (software)|After Dark]]'' for Windows, one of the most popular utilities ever made.{{citation needed|date=December 2017}} Software Dynamics created ''[[Operation: Inner Space]]'', one of the first Windows action games.{{citation needed|date=December 2017}} They have also created recent Windows applications such as Power Drawers published under their "Dynamic Karma" division and do design and development work on web browsers as well as creating new software.
