{{Infobox television | show_name = The Super Serious Show | image = The super serious show logo.jpg | image_size = 200px | show_name_2 = | genre = [[Comedy]], [[Variety show|Variety]], Improv | creator = CleftClips | based_on = | developer = | writer = | director = | creative_director = | presenter = | starring = | judges = | voices = | narrated = | theme_music_composer = | opentheme = | endtheme = | composer = | country = | language = | num_seasons = | num_episodes = | list_episodes = | executive_producer = | producer = CleftClips | editor = | location = [[Los Angeles]], [[United States]] | cinematography = | camera = | runtime = | company = | distributor = | channel = | picture_format = | audio_format = | first_run = | first_aired = | last_aired = | preceded_by = | followed_by = | related = [[Hot Tub Variety Show]] | website = http://hottubshow.tumblr.com/ | website_title = Hot Tub with Kurt & Kristen | production_website = http://www.cleftclips.com/ | production_website_title = CleftClips }}
'''''The Super Serious Show''''' is a live comedy show that mixes [[Stand-up comedy|stand-up]], [[Sketch comedy|sketch]], [[musical comedy]] and videos from a blend of up-and-coming performers and established comedians.<ref>{{cite web|last=Kroeger |first=Jake |url=http://www.serialoptimist.com/comedians-2/comedy-done-right-the-super-serious-show-5784.html |title=Comedy Done Right: The Super Serious Show |publisher=Serialoptimist.com |date= |accessdate=2014-03-10}}</ref> Embracing a wide variety of non-polished acts and spontaneity, ''The Super Serious Show'' combines elements of tradition club comedy and [[alternative comedy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://turnstylenews.com/2011/04/20/super-serious-comedy-producer-joel-mandelkorn-talks-live-comedy |title=Super Serious Comedy: Producer Joel Mandelkorn Talks Live Comedy |publisher=Turnstylenews.com |date=2011-04-20 |accessdate=2014-03-10}}</ref> The show is often a platform for well-known comics to test new material and "riff," or perform without any planned content. The monthly Los Angeles event features a D.J., food trucks, free food and wine, along with surprise appearances from special guests.<ref>[http://www.laweekly.com/bestof/2012/award/best-off-the-beaten-path-stand-up-comedy-party-1889824/ Los Angeles Best Off-the-Beaten-Path Stand-Up Comedy Party - The Super Serious Show at Cafe Club Fais Do-Do - Best Of Los Angeles - LA Weekly<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> In addition to the L.A. installment, the show tours the comedy festival circuit and has appeared at the [[Edinburgh Festival Fringe]], Riot L.A., and [[South by Southwest]] in conjunction with [[Funny or Die]] and [[SoundCloud]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chortle.co.uk/news/2012/05/30/15494/whats_in_tomorrows_edinburgh_fringe_programme%3F |title=What's in tomorrow's Edinburgh Fringe programme? : News 2012 : Chortle : The UK Comedy Guide |publisher=Chortle |date=2012-05-30 |accessdate=2014-03-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/samantha-pitchel/sxsw-comedy-day-3_b_1342863.html |title=Samantha Pitchel: SXSW Comedy Recap: Day 3 |publisher=Huffingtonpost.com |date= |accessdate=2014-03-10}}</ref> Notable past performers include [[Daniel Tosh]], [[Sarah Silverman]], [["Weird Al" Yankovic]], [[Amy Schumer]], [[Aisha Tyler]], [[Aziz Ansari]], [[Chris Kattan]], [[T.J. Miller]], [[Reggie Watts]], [[Margaret Cho]], [[Demetri Martin]], [[Kristen Schaal]], and [[John Hodgman]].
